maml:description.maml:para: Add an element.

Adds the specified element to the network list. If the network list's type is `IP`, the value needs to be a URL-encoded IP address or CIDR block. If the type is `GEO`, it's a two-character country code.
Unique identifier for each network list.
Specifies the element to add to the network list.

Get a network list.
Gets all network lists or retrieves a specific network list by its ID. When listing all, you can filter the results by name with the `-Search` parameter or by type with the `-ListType` parameter.
Account Switch Key, for use when you have access to mulitple accounts and need to specify which one to use. Account Switch Keys can be found using Get-AccountSwitchKey.
EdgeRC file to authenticate your command. Defaults to ~/.edgerc.

Provide additional response data identifying who created and updated the list and when, and the network list's deployment status in both `STAGING` and `PRODUCTION` environments. This data takes longer to provide.
If enabled, the response `list` includes all items. For large network lists, this may slow responses and yield large response objects. The default `true` value includes the list's contents.
Filters the output to lists of only the given type of network lists if provided, either IP or GEO. This corresponds to the network list object's type member.
Only list items that match the specified substring in any network list's name or list of items.

Update a network list.

Modifies the network list items and properties. You can edit the name, description, and set of network list items to the resource. You can't edit the type. When running the operation, the current state of the list is replaced with the properties and items you provide. > Note: To retrieve a network list with its elements, run the `Get-NetworkList` operation with the `-NetworkListID` parameter and the `-IncludeElements` switch, edit the content locally, and pipe it to this command. Make sure to use the `-IncludeElements` switch when retrieving. Otherwise, the operation won't return any elements.
Unique identifier for each network list.
